text.section:
The county superintendent and his professional assistants shall:
Visit the schools;
Observe their management and instruction;
Give suggestions for their improvement;
Consult with and advise principals and teachers; and
Try in every way to awaken public interest and improve educational conditions in the county.

The county superintendent shall prepare and recommend for adoption by the county board:
Curriculum guides;
Courses of study;
Resource material; and
Other teaching aids.

section.section:
The county superintendent shall prepare lists of the following items needed by the schools:
Textbooks;
Supplementary readers;
Materials of instruction;
Visual and auditory aids;
Stationery and school supplies; and
School furniture, equipment, and apparatus.
